title: North Korea Launches Unidentified Projectile Off Its East Coast, South Korea Says
sub_head: Type of weapon and location of launch weren’t immediately shared by Seoul’s military
body:
SEOUL—North Korea has launched an unidentified projectile off its east coast on Sunday morning, Seoul’s military said, restarting weapons tests after nearly a month of inaction.
The type of weapon, the flight distance traveled and location of the launch weren’t immediately shared by Seoul’s military.
